\f0\fs20 \cf0 Floating charges are debt secured by an entire business. In the event of default, the creditor with a floating-charge lien is granted control rights of the firm with little judicial interference. An alternative simply removes the specific regulation referring to automatic stays. This may, however, enable borrowers to secure multiple loans with a single asset and exacerbate lender co-ordination problems[#Jackson1986,Baird1986].}

